definitions.definition: The late period of the Roman Empire , following the principate , during which the emperor 's rule became more explicitly autocratic and remaining vestiges of the Roman Republic were removed from the formal workings of government ; the reign of any particular emperor during this period.

main_definition: ( historical ) The late period of the Roman Empire , following the principate , during which the emperor 's rule became more explicitly autocratic and remaining vestiges of the Roman Republic were removed from the formal workings of government ; the reign of any particular emperor during this period.
